blasted/shot too early.<br><br>With this tactic, I could not really stand up and fight, because i had to wait for the mobs to get back to thier spawn point to clear aggro. Or, if our groups killd the mob quickly, I would stand, let them reaggro on me, and repeat.<br><br>We could manage to clear the Courtyard, and the side AWAY from the temple, temple I was scared to try to pull.. ton of mobs in small area.<br><br>Anyway, I would appreciate any tips, advice, etc.<br><br>Btw, I did manage to snag a Wu's stick last night from a guild member that looted one =)<br><br>so, I retired one of my batons, and now have wu/baton (WU in primary)<br><br>My wife Got a Wrathbone warhammer, also =) I also managed to get 2 bubbles of exp from a pretty slow pulling night. ;/<br><br>It picked up at the end, I hope to do better tonight, faster exp, and HOPEFULLY another wu's before we end our tour of CoM. =)<br><br>Thanks!<br><br>Level 33 Iksar monkey now <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ustouthbound.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stouthbound</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(11/6/00 8:01:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pulling CoM</span><hr size=1> How Phaedreus Ashenfist eats a Reeses peanut butter cup:<br>Er...Pulls city of mist:<br><br>The easiest way to pull this place, without using the "stack them at the lamp" exploit (which GMs on Bertox always seem to be popping in to check), is to chain pull everything to the gate.  You can aggro basically the entire zone, and go to in front of that statue right inside the gate, and FD when some of the mobs are standing on you.<br><br>They'll start to walk away, and when they get as far away from the statue as to the entrance of the balconies, have someone run in and grab the one mob that's still standing on you.  This can be done usually just by running up and smacking it, as the mobs usually space themselves out pretty nicely.<br><br>Larger mobs spawn at the temple area than in the courtyard and gate area, so you may want to hold off on pulling that section until you have a larger group.  Other than that, the gate, courtyard, and stables are a good pull.<br><br>Depending on your swimming skill, and if you can get sow or not in your group, you may want to be ballsy and try and pull the big goo from the arena.  You could of course throw a shuriken at it and just run, but that's no fun :)  Best way I always do this is jump right on the island with it, kick it, and jump into the water.  Swim your way out to the lantern and hop up onto the land, the goo will either join you or run back through the zone, taking a (hopefully) cleared path to your group.  The big goo is around level 45-47, and is a fun kill for a fair bit of exp on an exciting pull. <p><a href="http://www.geocities.com/matttnusss/phaedreus.jpg">Phaedreus Ashenfist</a><br>Monk of the Lost Circle<br>Bertoxxulous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ufaang243.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faang243</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(11/6/00 8:52:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ahhh</span><hr size=1> Thanks Stouthbound, I was wondering how to pull the big goo, the higher level members of the other group in our guild wanted me to pull that guy, but I couldn't figure out how to get his attention, and I was scared to just throw something at him =)<br><br>Will have to try him tonight..<br><br>Again, I was thinking about setting up camp right outside of the goo temple, but I was scared to move away from a zoneline being my first time =)<br><br>Thanks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ustouthbound.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stouthbound</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(11/6/00 8:56:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ahhh</span><hr size=1> If you guys are camping right outside the goo temple (the arena place), you can stand on the ledge that runs around the stone pillar that the big too stands on and throw a shuriken at him.  He'll crawl down over the pillar and up the wall of the ledge and give you a big hug. <p><a href="http://www.geocities.com/matttnusss/phaedreus.jpg">Phaedreus Ashenfist</a><br>Monk of the Lost Circle<br>Bertoxxulous</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ucatharz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Catharz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 183<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(11/29/00 2:42:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://shadowstar-alliance.com/MemberPages/screenshots/catharz.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pulling CoM</span><hr size=1> I found CoM to be one of the easiest places to pull singles.  Lots of static spawns.<br><br>If I'm near the zone I'll pull to just past the gates, FD and wait for 2 mobs to hit their spawn points.  As soon as they do, I stand up and (if I time it right) I get a single every time.<br><br>But my favorite spot in CoM is the area just north of the arena where the big goo is.  Sit the group in the middle of that area, pull goos from the arena room, FD at the door and wait until most are at their spawn points, stand up, if 2 come FD again, rinse &amp; repeat until you have 1.<br><br>Once the goos are clear, pull the house to the west of your group through it's south end door.  Open the door and 2 mobs will come out.  FD, wait a few seconds, stand (one will usually be back at it's spawn point by then) and pull the single.  Then pull the other spawn from that end, then the two from the other end (feigning in the middle of the house).<br><br>I then move to the house south/west of the arena room and pull the 3 lumpies there.  I drag them out of the house and FD outside the north door.  Same tactics as the first spawns in the north house.  Wait a few seconds, then stand up.<br><br>By the time I pull from there the lumpies in the arena room are normally ready to go again.<br><br>The hardest thing I find about CoM is pulling the captain area clear to get your group to the arena area.  You need a good group (or crowd control) to take the mobs down quickly enough to clear the way. <p><table width="275"><tr><td bgcolor="#000000" align="center" cellpadding="3"><font size="3" color="#CC9900"><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=32202">Catharz Doshu</a> (Level 41 Human Monk)<br><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=12223">Ssleazy Sslizard</a> (Level 20 Iksar Shaman)</font><br><a href="http://www.shadowstar-alliance.com" target="_top"><img src="http://shadowstar-alliance.com/images/SSA2.jpg" width="250" height="75" border="0"></a></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap 