ith me, and we will have a good time! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uxorshaik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xorshaik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(2/15/01 11:35:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tha door?</span><hr size=1> Wonder if what you're referring to (I'm not sufficiently familiar to know for sure) is the door that every time I've been on a raid the leader says DON'T GO THROUGH THE DOOR. hehe. There's some secret wall that we went through next to this one. I think this was said to a raid with about 6 or 7 groups 43-60, mostly 50+ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ucelesteawildrose.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celestea Wildrose</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(2/16/01 2:17:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hsian-li.tripod.com/bouncie.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tha door?</span><hr size=1> CoM has had pathing changes... the stacking at the lamp no longer works, mobs just go through that wall like it doesn't exist, after porting deep in and porting back with about 10 friends. Pulling to the  zone line doesn't work anymore if anything is blue <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p><br><img src="http://hsian-li.tripod.com/celesteasignature.jpg" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uzinj.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zinj</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 1080<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(3/26/01 7:46:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pulling CoM</span><hr size=1> Icklymuk<br>    Disciple<br>    posts: 110<br>    (3/23/01 10:41:00 am)<br>    Reply | Edit | Del All<br>                      CoM Reaver Guide... Feedback wanted...<br><br>                      Heres a guide I did for my guide, that I would like to share with you guys. I've<br>                      already gotten some great feed back on this, and any more, tips and tactic's would<br>                      be great...<br><br>                      ** Updated as of 3/23/2001<br><br><br>                      *********************************************<br><br><br><br>                      This Guide will cover strategies on how to defeat the reavers in the City of Mist.<br><br>                      Click here to see a map of the first floor, showing the connection between the<br>                      entrance back to the castle area. This map also shows the tunnel connections<br>                      through out this zone, labeled B through E.<br><br>                      Click here to see a map of sky area within City of Mist.<br><br>                      Let me start this with a quick primer for those that not familiar with the City of Mist.<br>                      The City of Mist is a dead and Ancient City of the Iksar.<br>                      The Shaman Quests actually reviles a large back story of this city and how it<br>                      incurred the wraith of Cazic-Thule.<br>                      You can read more on this here ...<br><br>                      When entering City of Mist you are first greeted by narrow corridors. Once you walk<br>                      around the first two corners you will actually see the beauty that is CoM. <br>                      The First thing you will surely notice is the large Gate before you. <br>                      The Next thing you're sure to notice are the two creatures beating on your unwary<br>                      back. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>                      As you can see CoM is laid out from a east to west fashion. The first area you come<br>                      too is the moat area. Across the moat spans a broken bridge, which leads to a<br>                      rather daunting Gate.<br>                      This Gate can easily be opened by clicking on it.<br>                      To either side of the moat area are the balconies. These can be accessed by<br>                      passing through the gate.<br><br>                      From the Gate, a left or a right will take you to the Court Yard area. To the Right of<br>                      the gate you can access the Court yard, the right balcony or the Temple.<br>                      To the left of the gate you can access the Courtyard, the left balcony, or the stable<br>                      area.<br><br>                      Past the Curt yard is the Arena.<br>                      If you are looking at the map its the section with the B on it. The Arena building<br>                      actually has a functional Arena inside of it. Be careful though as this area is usually<br>                      guarded by high level Goo's.<br><br>                      On either side of the arena is a set of houses. These houses are home to a number<br>                      of creatures. It should be noted that caution is recommended when going past these<br>                      areas.<br><br>                      Now we are almost to the castle area. This is were the guide will try to focus in on.<br><br>                      The Castle area.<br><br>                      Past the Arena and the Houses lies two &quot;roads&quot; to the castle. Most guilds that I<br>                      have seen stage raids here will try to setup on the south side of the zone. The area<br>                      from the houses to the first corner is usually clear of spawns.<br>                      The Corner areas on both the north and the south side have a 3 or 4 spawn pattern.<br>                      Once these are cleared you can move to the areas labeled Camp Spot.<br>                      The South area isn't labeled but can be used just the same.<br>                      The Octagonal areas past the camp spot hold 3 spawns each. Once these are<br>                      cleared its time that your puller and a rogue make their way to the castle door.<br>                      It should be noted that the Captain of the Guard is reported to have a key to this<br>                      door, but as of yet I haven't seen this to be the case.<br><br>                      Within the Castle there are 4 spawns on each side of the wall. Toward the back of<br>                      the first room is a broken Throne. This is where the first reaver is to be found.<br>                      With a good puller its possible to pull everything out before you engage the Reaver.<br>                      If the puller is too low, it is common to expect the entire room. Eight Spawns plus<br>                      the Reaver.<br><br>                      For those that have never encountered a reaver let me explain just a bit about<br>                      them.<br>                      Reavers look like the Golem from Cazic-Thule zone. They are big ugly black things.<br>                      They are 100% magic resistant, meaning they can't be charmed or slowed. They<br>                      average around level 51, in most cases. They hit really fast and hard, and on top of<br>                      that they blind. When killed they either have a chance to spawn another reaver, a<br>                      ghost type mob common to CoM, or One of the 3 Lords. I have heard of a rare case<br>                      of up to 12 reavers spawning before the Lord did. /nasty<br><br>                      Once the first room is clear and you are ready to take on your first reaver, make<br>                      sure your primary healers and wizards are at full mana. The first reaver most<br>                      commonly spawns Lord Gorik. For the most part this Lord will spawn after 1 to 3<br>                      reavers have been killed. <br>                      Lord Gorik him self is fairly easy.<br>                      Again he's 100% magic resident and only Lure type spells will effect him.<br><br>                      Lord Gorik drops include he mace of the shadowed souls and the books for the<br>                      shaman quests.<br><br>                      I shall cover Neh'Ashiir next, commonly considered the second reaver in line to die.<br><br>                      To get to the Queen of CoM, the raid party should, after the First reaver has been<br>                      killed, move into the Castle area.<br>                      You will notice two doors on the back side of the first room. You'll want to lead your<br>                      raid thru the right door. Once the raid has come to the corner you'll want to stop<br>                      and clear the way before you.<br>                      Once you are at the right hand corner you will see a ramp leading upwards. You are<br>                      now inside the wall along the North camp site. This area commonly has goo's roming<br>                      the area.<br>                      Once the hall way is clear up too, the Section labeled A, lead your guild up to<br>                      around -200. This is a tight hall way for a large raid like this, so make due.<br><br>                      At this point your necro's should start handing out Dead Man Floating to EVERYONE<br>                      at the raid.<br>                      You are about to enter a section that one slip will mean your death.<br><br>                      Please refer to this map now.<br><br>                      Click here to see a map of sky area within City of Mist.<br><br>                      The Area Marked with an A is actually right before a door. This door leads further<br>                      into the castle with common mobs found through out City of Mist. This can be<br>                      ignored.<br>                      To the Right of this door is a fake wall.<br>                      Steping through this wall is a clear cat walk, leading up to the first Sky house. This<br>                      is were your guild will thank your necros for DMF. It is important to make sure<br>                      everyone is aware of this. These Catwalks are confusing and every raid I've seen go<br>                      up it, someone always drops.<br><br>                      Our Pullers always pulled the first house to the raid waiting within the hallway before<br>                      going up the ramp.<br><br>                      The first house in the sky area has 3 rooms in it. I believe there are a total of 8 or<br>                      so mobs within these rooms. If you've gotten to this point this shouldn't be an issue.<br>                      Work your way through the first house and on to the bridge beyond.<br>                      Unfortunately this map has no detail of the inside of these houses.<br><br>                      Once you have made it past the first house you'll want to take your guild to the first<br>                      corner. Your Puller and rogue will now head to the second house. This is the second<br>                      door that requires a rogue. It was customary that the rogue would stay at the door<br>                      opening as needed for the puller, until the raid was through.<br><br>                      The Second House has several more spawns. I believe around 6. These are of course<br>                      pulled to the corner where the raid is waiting.<br><br>                      Once the House is cleared the raid is moved into the house and the pullers will now<br>                      start pulling the romers between House2 and House3.<br>                      Once the Romers are cleared, its time to move the raid up to the corner between<br>                      house2 and house3.<br>                      At this point you will want to buff you raid party. Neh'Ashiir doesn't dispel. So this is<br>                      just a standard max buff session.<br>                      As you can see from the map the bridge before House3 is broken. With DMF this can<br>                      easily be passed over, if you are quick about it.<br><br>                      House3 also requires a rogue to open.<br>                      So not only do you have a locked door, but you also have a broken bridge in front of<br>                      it to deal with as well.<br>                      Once the Raid party is set and ready for this finial encounter, its a simple matter of<br>                      rushing the reaver.<br>                      House3 is pretty small space. On either side there is a set of steps leading up to a<br>                      plat form where the reaver spawns.<br>                      The floor under this platform is fake.<br><br>                      I'll repeat that for everyone, cause I'm sure you missed it.<br>                      The floor under the platform is fake!<br>                      Make sure EVERYONE is aware of this.<br><br>                      Its most important to fight the reaver and Neh'Ashiir with your backs to the fake<br>                      floor. I have seen Neh'Ashiir fall through this hole and start summoning people.<br>                      Luckily when she did this, she summoned me and they warped back up top. I knew<br>                      for sure we were all going to die.<br><br>                      Once Neh'Ashiir has spawned the raid can take a few second to clean up any deaths<br>                      that happened from the reaver. As she spawns Non agro now for the Shaman<br>                      quests.<br><br><br>                      Before the fight begins your Raid shaman should turn in his/her epic quest piece.<br><br>                      Once Neh'Ashiir is dead. The raid should jump down, with DMF on and try to float<br>                      toward the camp spot, Marked on the first map.<br><br>                      Lord Rak'Ashiir.<br><br>                      Lord Rak'Ashiir is the finial spawn in the shaman epic Quest. I'm sure everyone will at<br>                      sometime get to meet this wonderful lord.<br>                      Getting to him isn't as painful as Neh'Ashiir, his queen. But in most cases it's more<br>                      challenging.<br><br>                      Lord Rak'Ashiir Occupies a loft just about the first room in the castle.<br>                      By looking at the map you will notice a triangle behind the back wall of the first<br>                      room.<br>                      This lift will take you into a room just before lord Rak.<br>                      This room is occupied by no less than 4 reavers.<br>                      It is of the UP most importance that you have your best/highest level pullers pull this<br>                      room.<br><br>                      These guardian reavers are commonly pulled to the Camp area marked on the map. <br><br>                      These reavers usually spawn a common undead mob after dieing, but they again can<br>                      spawn another reaver, caution is the key here.<br><br>                      The anti chamber has a set of steps leading up to lord Rak's room.<br>                      Within Lord Rak's room is another set of reavers. 4 again I believe.<br>                      These area again pulled out side.<br>                      Once the finial reaver has been killed and Lord Rak spawns. Every one in your raid<br>                      should back off... This is a job that requires some pop corn and a coke.<br>                      To Combat Lord Rak, the raid needs to have at least two 49 level mages.<br><br>                      Since Lord Rak doesn't spawn agro the raid will have a few minutes to buff and make<br>                      ready.<br><br>                      At this time the mages should summon fire pets.<br>                      Once Summoned the mages should instruct the clerics and shaman to throw every<br>                      HP and AC buff they have at the pets.<br><br>                      Once the buff process for the pets is finished, its time to start the fight.<br><br>                      Lord Rak Ashiir.<br>                      Level 60 has 15K in HPS and as an AE fire proc that does around 1.5K in damage.<br>                      Now you can respect the fire pets for saving you.<br><br>                      If the Raid has a Shaman this shaman should turn in his epic Quest item and hope<br>                      that he/she doesn't die from the first AE proc. Rak will immediately become agro.<br>                      This is when the Fire pets are sent in.<br>                      Cleric should keep an eye on HPS .<br>                      If nothing goes wrong, Rak should be dead within a few minutes, and the raid should<br>                      have suffered little or no deaths.<br>                      You will also have one happy shaman...<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>                                                **Updated notes**<br><br><br>                      Eliezar suggested a wonderfull idea for pulling Neh'Ashiir.<br><br>                      &quot;We find that pulling Neh`Ashiir's reaver to the middle building in the air is solid.<br>                      There is no hole in the floor to fall through. I'd even advise that only the puller ever<br>                      enter the 3rd hut. &quot;<br><br>                      Buguk Uguk pointed out something that I hadn't ever thought of... And supprised a<br>                      few other people as well.<br><br>                      &quot;The City of Mist is an outdoor zone. What class(es) excel(s) in the Great Outdoors?<br>                      Bring your friendly neighborhood ranger or druid (ranger is preferred for their AC) to<br>                      help pull the 4 black reaver room with Harmony. We were able to easily pull them one<br>                      at a time down to the throne room.&quot;<br><br>                      Edited by: Icklymuk at: 3/23/01 12:02:03 pm<br>    Iskax DaIksar<br>    Disciple<br>    posts: 82<br>    (3/23/01 1:09:43 pm)<br>    Reply | Edit | Del<br>                      Re: CoM Reaver Guide... Feedback wanted...<br><br>                      Reavers are on a 2hour spawn timer, sorry if this was included and i missed it.<br><br>                      --Sezar <br>    Icklymuk<br>    Disciple<br>    posts: 112<br>    (3/23/01 2:03:23 pm)<br>    Reply | Edit | Del<br>                      Re: Co